  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study objective is to evaluate the benefits of Oral Nutritional Supplementation (ONS)
      plus Dietary Counseling (DC) in newly admitted hospital subjects with moderate or severe
      malnutrition.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Approximately 212 subjects (men and women) from multiple Institutions in India will
      participate in this study. Eligible subjects will be randomized into 2 treatment groups.

        -  Dietary Counseling only (n=106)

        -  Dietary Counseling + ONS (n=106)
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
